<h2>API DOCUMENTATION</h2>

{{!-- =============== CATEGORIES =================== --}}
<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Categories</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">

    <ul class="list-group">
      <li class="list-group-item">
        <h4> <span class="label label-success">GET</span> <code>'api/categories/:id?' </code></h4>
        <p>Gets all the categories, or given an id returns a specific category</p>
        <p>Returns either an array of category objects, OR a single category object (when given :id) 
          OR <code>null</code> if (there is no category for the given id)
        </p>
      </li>

    </ul>

  </div>
</div>

{{!-- =============== USERS =================== --}}
<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Users</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">

    <ul class="list-group">
      <li class="list-group-item">
        <h4> <span class="label label-success">GET</span> <code>'api/users/:id?' </code></h4>
        <p>Gets all the users, or given an id returns a specific user</p>
        <p> Returns either an array of user objects, OR a single user object (when given :id) 
          OR <code>null</code> if (there is no user for the given id)
        </p>
        <p>* Excludes the password_hash for return all users objects</p>
      </li>
      <li class="list-group-item">
        <h4> <span class="label label-success">GET</span> <code>'api/users/:user_id/:searchTerm' </code></h4>
        <p>Gets a user object & associated table data based off the given <code>:searchTerm</code></p>
        <p>Options for <code>:searchTerm</code> include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>categories {array}</code> : returns a user object with a key of "Categories" </li>
          <li><code>quizzess-taken {array}</code>  : returns a user object with a key of "Quizzes" </li>
          <li><code>quizzess-made {array}</code> : returns a user object with a key of "QuizzessMade" </li>
          <li><code>posts {array}</code> : returns a user object with a key of "Posts"</li>
        </ul>
        <p> * code is written forgivingly, so if a searchTerm doesn't match or exist, a simple user object is returned if they exist. And null if they don't exist </p>
      </li>

    </ul>

  </div>
</div>

